{
    "analysis": "We detected many consecutive anomaly sequences across multiple components and KPIs in the incident window (2021-03-23 16:30 → 17:00 Asia/Shanghai). Key observations from metric fault identification: \n- Several component-KPIs are anomalous for the entire window (seq_length=31), including: IG01 JVM-Memory_NoHeapMemoryUsed (constant high value), MG02 process/agent related KPIs, and many Tomcat04 Tomcat-Requests KPIs (ErrorCount, MaxTime, Processing, RequestCount etc.).\n- Some shorter anomaly bursts exist in Tomcat02 and intermittent short bursts in Tomcat04 zabbix agent KPI.\n- Because multiple service-level candidates (Tomcat02, Tomcat04) and an application JVM node (IG01) show sustained anomalies, we cannot pick a single root cause from metrics alone. According to the diagnosis rules, when multiple service-level faulty components exist we should use traces to identify the most downstream faulty service in the call chain, and use logs to disambiguate resource-level reasons.\nWhat should be done next: perform trace analysis to find which service(s) have trace-feature anomalies (e.g., elevated self duration, increased downstream spans, or call errors) during the incident window. This will help identify which service is the most downstream faulty component among the metric candidates.",
